      "content": "It's important to understand that even a single glass of wine can interact with zolpidem. Alcohol can enhance the sedative effects of zolpidem, leading to increased drowsiness, impaired coordination, and slower reaction times. This can be especially dangerous when you're trying to drive or operate machinery. The combination could also lead to more severe side effects, such as respiratory depression or even overdose. It's always best to follow your doctor's advice and avoid alcohol while taking zolpidem. There are other ways to relax and prepare for sleep that don't involve risking your health.",
      "source": "target",
